%I A394617 #35 Jul 21 2026 22:36:31
%S A394617 1,1,1,2,1,2,1,5,2,2,1,5,1,2,1,14,1,5,1,5,2,2,1,15,2,2,5,4,1,4,1,50,1,
%T A394617 2,1,14,1,2,2,14,1,6,1,4,2,2,1,52,2,5,1,5,1,15,2,13,2,2,1,13,1,2,4,
%U A394617 259,1,4,1,5,1,4,1,50,1,2,3,4,1,6,1
%N A394617 Number of 4-generated groups of order n: groups that have a generating set of size <= 4.
%C A394617 a(n) = A000001(n) whenever n has at most four prime factors since all non-cyclic simple groups are generated by 2 elements, and if G=HK then the size of the minimum generating set of G is at most the sum of the sizes of minimum generating sets of H and K.
%C A394617 a(n) first differs from A066389(n) when n=8 and from A396721(n) when n=16.
%H A394617 Adam Onus, <a href="/A394617/b394617.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..511</a>
%H A394617 Rashid Barket, Enrico Grimaldi, Yacoub Hendi, Edward Hirst, Adam Onus, and Harmeet Singh, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.12026">Learning the Graphical Nature of Symmetries</a>, arXiv:2607.12026 [stat.ML], 2026. See p. 9.
%e A394617 a(p) = 1 for p prime since the unique group of order p is cyclic.
%e A394617 a(16) = 14 because there are 14 groups of order 16 and all can be generated by four elements.
%e A394617 a(32) = 50 because there are 51 groups of order 32 and only (C_2)^5 cannot be generated by four elements.
%o A394617 (SageMath) lambda n : sum([len(sage.interfaces.gap.gap.MinimalGeneratingSet(G)) <= 4 for G in sage.interfaces.gap.gap(n).AllSmallGroups()])
%Y A394617 Cf. A000001, A066389, A396721.
%K A394617 nonn,new
%O A394617 1,4
%A A394617 _Adam Onus_, Jun 18 2026
